-- Mexico Stocks: Banregio, Genomma Lab, Penoles Shares Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-04-02T17:46:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/mexico-stocks-banregio-genomma-lab-penoles-shares-are-active.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of 11:55 a.m. in Mexico City.  The IPC index rose 0.9 percent to 39,872.73.  Genomma Lab Internacional SAB (LABB)  , the Mexican
producer of over-the-counter drugs, climbed 1.1 percent to 23.57
pesos as UBS AG reiterated its buy recommendation. A research
note dated today from Marimar Torreblanca, an analyst in Mexico
City, said it “is trading at a very attractive level,” whether
or not Prestige Brands Holdings Inc. accepts Genomma’s
unsolicited bid.  Banregio Grupo Financiero SAB (GFREGIO)  (GFREGIO MM), the Mexican
bank that held an initial public offering last year, climbed 2.8
percent to 35.88 pesos. Citigroup Inc.’s Banamex unit reiterated
its buy recommendation on Banregio, saying it’s among the “best
positioned” banks to benefit from an increase in credit to
small and medium-sized businesses.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer and a miner of gold, climbed 2 percent to 633
pesos. Gold advanced after economic reports signaled improving
demand in  China  and the U.S. Silver also climbed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
